author: lemifn
description: In response to declining birth rates and shrinking student populations, some rural schools in South Korea have enrolled elderly women-particularly grandmothers who never had the opportunity to learn to read or write-to keep their classrooms open. For example, Bangrim Primary School in Gangwon Province, which once had nearly 700 students, saw its enrollment drop to just 22. To prevent closure, the school began admitting elderly women like 72-year-old Park Go-ee, who now attends classes alongside much younger students to learn the literacy skills she missed earlier in life. This initiative not only helps sustain rural schools but also offers lifelong learning opportunities for seniors, enhancing their social inclusion and mental well-being. Studies have shown that literacy education for rural seniors in South Korea is positively linked to greater social inclusion and improved mental health. As South Korea continues to grapple with one of the world's lowest fertility rates, such innovative approaches serve a dual purpose: preserving educational institutions in rural areas and empowering elderly citizens through education. #fyp #blowup #story #school

author: richardakers27
description: Ozzy Osbourne, born John Michael Osbourne on December 3, 1948, in Birmingham, England, is a pioneering figure in heavy metal music, renowned for his distinctive voice, charismatic stage presence, and tumultuous career. Often referred to as the "Prince of Darkness," Osbourne has had a profound influence on rock music and popular culture, both as the frontman of Black Sabbath and as a solo artist. Osbourne's early life was marked by economic hardship and a rebellious spirit. Growing up in a working-class family in Birmingham, he faced numerous challenges, including a troubled academic career and a series of odd jobs. His passion for music emerged during his teenage years, and he eventually joined the band Earth, which would later become Black Sabbath. In 1968, Black Sabbath was formed with Osbourne as the lead vocalist, alongside guitarist Tony Iommi, bassist Geezer Butler, and drummer Bill Ward. The band's self-titled debut album, released in 1970, is often credited with pioneering heavy metal music. Black Sabbath's dark, heavy sound and Osbourne's distinctive voice set the stage for a new genre and influenced countless bands that followed. Black Sabbath's 1970 release, "Paranoid," further cemented their place in rock history with iconic tracks like "Iron Man," "War Pigs," and the title track "Paranoid." The album's success solidified Osbourne's reputation as a leading figure in the heavy metal genre. His theatrical stage presence and powerful vocals became defining characteristics of the band's performances. Despite the band's success, Osbourne's tenure with Black Sabbath was marked by internal conflicts and his own struggles with substance abuse. The pressures of fame and the lifestyle associated with it took a toll on Osbourne, leading to his departure from the band in 1979. His departure was a significant turning point, both for him and for Black Sabbath, who continued to have success with different lineups. In 1980, Ozzy Osbourne launched his solo career with the release of "Blizzard of Ozz," an album that introduced a new chapter in his career. The album featured hit songs like "Crazy Train" and "Mr. Crowley," showcasing Osbourne's ability to blend melodic elements with his heavy metal roots. The success of the album marked the beginning of Osbourne's successful solo career and established him as a major force in rock music. Osbourne's solo career continued to thrive throughout the 1980s and 1990s with a series of successful albums, including "Diary of a Madman" (1981) and "No More Tears" (1991). His music during this period maintained his heavy metal edge while also exploring new themes and styles. Hits like "Mama, I'm Coming Home" and "No More Tears" became staples of his live performances. Despite ongoing health issues and various personal challenges, including his battle with Parkinson's disease, Osbourne has continued to tour and record new music. His influence on heavy metal and rock music remains significant, and his contributions to the genre have been recognized with numerous awards and honors. Ozzy Osbourne's impact on music and culture is profound. He is often credited with shaping the sound of heavy metal and influencing countless artists who have followed in his footsteps. His career, marked by both remarkable achievements and notable controversies, has established him as one of rock's most enduring and iconic figures. Overall, Ozzy Osbourne's legacy is characterized by his innovative approach to heavy metal, his larger-than-life persona, and his ability to connect with audiences through his music and performances. description: Amber Portwood's Terse Response to an Honest Text from Daughter Leah Shocks Teen Mom Cast and Fans - At Gary's home, Leah explains to him and Kristina that she wants to send Amber a text that clarifies where they stand. "I have a text ready that I want to send to Amber and get it over with," Leah tells them. In a confessional, she explains, "Obviously, for the past few years, I've been feeling a certain way. But the last straw was when she was doing her lives online. To say what she said...she was even talking about me some. I, personally, can't handle it." - The text says... "This isn't mean to hurt you but I want to let you know that all these years it's been my decision to not have a relationship with you and nobody has influenced my decision. I feel like recent online activities have put me in a place where I need to communicate this to put a boundary between us for myself," Leah reads. She tells Kristina, "I just wanted to keep it short and not go off or anything, because I feel like that's just kind of immature." Leah acknowledges she's "scared," but sends the message. In a confessional, Leah says, "I would say I have a hard time forgiving and forgetting and stuff like that. The best way for me to forgive her would be me moving on, but I'm really glad that I made my own move to actually push forward for myself and what I want, so I just hope that she's finding a way to accept it." - Cameras catch up with Amber later as she receives it. "Why is Leah messaging me?" she asks the producer she's working with. Amber reads the message and explains it to the producer, taking a minute to process before beginning to go off about Gary. "And then you have this other piece of s---, nasty man, this is the s--- that [I] get from my daughter that I love so much and I can't even give her it?" Amber began. "I can't take her out on little dates like I did with my son. I couldn't take her out to go shopping, I couldn't take her out to f--king eat alone," she continued. "Gary said I had to go over there, you nasty prick." Then, she addressed her daughter. "And Leah? Stop. You're 16. Stop!" She looked right into the camera before continuing, saying, "People see the disrespect, by the way, and they tell me how much you disrespect me too, stop!" "You're rude. There's no reason to be rude. You do not know what you are saying right now," she continued. "You're young, be young. Be 16. Be 16 and do not be in the middle of me and your father!" - Several Teen Mom castmates reacted to the intense scene. Mackenzie Douthit answered an Instagram Q&A question on the moment by writing, "I'm not gonna lie, I stopped and said a prayer that Leah would never see that." On her Snapchat, Cheyenne Floyd Davis posted the scene with mind-blown emojis, while Jade Cline made mention of it in her episode recap. "The way she looked into that camera and started basically going off on her own child that is saying, 'Hey, it's me. I'm the one making this choice because you're doing things that are, they're hurting me and I'm a 16 year old and I'm having a hard time processing and dealing with it,'" she began. Jade says Amber maintains a "victim mentality" and says, "It's okay to be accountable and make mistakes." "I think that's what kids look for, is someone to apologize and say they f---ed up and then actively start doing things to show, 'Hey, I'm being better, I'm trying to be better. I'm doing things differently for you.' I think that's essentially what Leah has been looking for and hasn't been getting it and she's over it." Leah Messer was asked about it on her Instagram Live and said, "I think when it comes to that‚Ä¶ it's none of my business. I don't want to get into other people's family dynamics and their challenges. But I just really feel like, no matter what the children, the kids, they have to be put first, and I couldn't imagine ‚Äî we just got to set ourselves aside and make it less about you and most about the children involved," she shared. #TeenMom #teenmomthenextchapter

description: Teen Mom‚Äôs Tyler Baltierra and Catelynn Lowell Vow Not to Mention Carly or Her Parents Anymore ‚Ä¢ Tyler Baltierra¬†and¬†Catelynn LowellCatelynn Lowell‚Äôs latest update on daughter Carly has led to some new perspectives. On the Thursday, May 22, episode of¬†Teen Mom: The Next Chapter, Dr.¬†Drew Pinsky¬†had a virtual meeting with the couple to recall a private conversation he had with Carly‚Äôs adoptive parents,¬†Brandon¬†and¬†Teresa Davis. ‚ÄúI can tell you what was expressed to me about Carly,‚Äù he shared on the MTV reality show‚Äôs season finale. ‚ÄúBrandon said she is thriving and she has friends and she‚Äôs athletic and musical and she‚Äôs doing all these wonderful things.‚Äù Catelynn tried to hold back tears as she wondered why Dr. Drew was sharing the update and not Carly‚Äôs adoptive parents. ‚ÄúWell thanks for keeping that beautiful girl away from me,‚Äù she said while getting visibly emotional. Dr. Drew replied, ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt think that‚Äôs the intent. I understand that‚Äôs how it feels. I know you. I know how tough this is. I get it.‚Äù ‚ÄúIn terms of being unblocked and a visit, I don‚Äôt see that not happening, frankly,‚Äù Dr. Drew shared. ‚ÄúYou got to go through the baby steps. But you are encouraged to send gifts on Christmas, birthdays and when gifts are completely appropriate.‚Äù While Tyler expressed his belief that it‚Äôs ‚Äúweird‚Äù to be getting this information from someone other than Brandon and Teresa, Dr. Drew explained that no situation is perfect. ‚Ä¢ ‚ÄúWhat Teresa kept saying is she absolutely wants what you want and wants to maintain a relationship, but she feels like she needs a reset and for everybody to calm down and let all the negativity [settle],‚Äù he said. ‚Äú[Carly] sings in church. She‚Äôs quite an accomplished singer and they recorded a song of hers. I would love to listen with you because it‚Äôs so moving. It does feel like Carly is sending a message of, ‚ÄòI‚Äôm good.‚Äô Do you guys want to hear it?‚Äù Citing her mental health, Catelynn said she wanted to listen in private. According to MTV, when she asked for the link to hear the performance, Brandon and Teresa denied the request. ‚Ä¢ In a joint statement on social media, both Carly and Tyler promised to not speak about Carly, Brandon and Teresa publicly moving forward. ‚ÄúBirthparents are always at the mercy of the adopters (which is understandable since we‚Äôre the ones who relinquished our baby to them) but that still doesn‚Äôt make it any less hard or painful,‚Äù Tyler and Catelynn wrote via Instagram on Thursday. ‚ÄúAs I‚Äôve stated before, we won‚Äôt be mentioning our biological daughter or her parents anymore & that‚Äôs why we‚Äôre actually relieved that this episode is airing, so that way we can all just finally move forward.‚Äù ‚ÄúWe are incredibly sorry if anything we have said about our truth as birthparents has hurt you or Carly or negatively impacted your life. That was never our intention,‚Äù the pair said in a letter to Brandon and Teresa. ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre the adults here & it‚Äôs our job to put everything aside for the best interest of Carly. Which requires open, honest & transparent communication. So we hope moving forward, you will participate in that requirement.‚Äù #teenmom #teenmomthenextchapter #teenmomfansfb #mtv #realitytv #fyp #teenager #usweekly #adoption #adoptionstory #openadoption #closedadpption #nocontact #instagram #message
